Perfect timing and venue for us to record a special episode of Startup Policy Forum’s series “IndiaAI in Action” - @emergentlabs hackathon
#Vibecon India in Bengaluru. 

We got @mukundjha to chat with  us about the future of vibe coding, Wingman -the latest AI agent he’s shipped, the ARR debate, his journey as a second-time founder and why he believes the AI cycle is under-hyped. 

Vibecon wrapped up yesterday and we captured the electric energy of hundreds of vibe coders in action! 

Winning team gets an interview with @ycombinator that hosted its Startup School in Bengaluru today after being flooded with 25,000 applications. 

